	<body id = 'pagebody'><p>I know that people using Lion will have nice, pretty scrollbars, but what about those of us who don't have Lion? I was wondering if we can add some iOS-like scrollbars to the site. I think that it would add more personality to the site.<br>
Example <a href="http://css-tricks.com/examples/WebKitScrollbars/" rel="nofollow noreferrer">here</a>:</p>

<p><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/eRc8W.png" alt="custom scrollbar"></p>

<p>Obviously we'd have to make the scrollbars grey...but that's simple.</p>

<p>EDIT: Here's the code:</p>

<pre><code>/* For the "inset" look only */
html {
    overflow: auto;
}
body {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1px;
    bottom: 1px;
    overflow-y: scroll;
    overflow-x: hidden;
}
/* Start Scrollbar */
::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 10px;
} 
/* Track */
::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
    -webkit-box-shadow: inset 0 0 1px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
    -webkit-border-radius: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
}
/* Handle */
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    -webkit-border-radius: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    -webkit-box-shadow: inset 0 0 45px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
}
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:window-inactive {
    background: rgba(255,0,0,0.4);
}
/* End Scrollbar */
</code></pre>

